                            <comment id="13471672" author="v.himanshu" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 17:03:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removing the hardcoded line picked correct surefire.version for localTests profile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471711" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 18:10:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Which pom.xml contains the 2.10 version ?&lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t see it in root pom.xml&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471729" author="v.himanshu" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 18:26:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see it in the trunk, under localTests profile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471829" author="nkeywal" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 20:20:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It wasn&apos;t really an accident. I&apos;ve done it this way because the private version included changes on the junit47 provider, but not on the junit4 provider (the later is used for local tests). Add to that that surefire is sometimes buggy, and it saves discussions around &quot;it would work with the official version&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not there in trunk anymore, I removed it in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6702&quot; title=&quot;ResourceChecker refinement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as the 2.10 contained a bug fixed in our private version that was needed after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6702&quot; title=&quot;ResourceChecker refinement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471839" author="v.himanshu" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 20:49:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the clarification &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nkeywal&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nkeywal&quot;&gt;Nicolas Liochon&lt;/a&gt;. (a basic mvn question:  So, we used a patched version of surefire? It&apos;s picked from which repo?).&lt;br/&gt;
Umm, on other hand, I also see that my local repo was not getting updated. Fixed that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471840" author="v.himanshu" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 20:49:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Already solved as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6702&quot; title=&quot;ResourceChecker refinement&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6702&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6702&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13471878" author="nkeywal" created="Mon, 8 Oct 2012 21:30:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Details are in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4955&quot; title=&quot;Use the official versions of surefire &amp;amp; junit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4955&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4955&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
